modules.description: Provides session management operations including generating, retrieving, updating, and removing session data. Works with string-based keys, string values, and integer-based expiration periods. Used to handle session lifecycles in web applications, ensuring timely expiration and secure storage of user-specific data.

Handles cookie-based session management and persistent storage for HTTP servers, using CoHTTP, Webmachine, Async, and Lwt. Operates on session identifiers, cookie headers, and backend storage structures like in-memory maps or file-based stores. Enables secure user authentication by tracking logged-in states across requests, allowing restricted access to endpoints until authentication is completed.

Manages web session data through operations that generate, retrieve, update, and delete sessions using string keys, string values, and integer expiration times. Sessions are stored with timed expiration to control lifecycle and ensure data freshness. Supports secure handling of user-specific information in web applications. Example tasks include storing user authentication tokens and clearing expired sessions.
